# CODEOWNERS
#
# This file defines who must review pull requests that touch specific paths.
# GitHub automatically requests reviews from the listed owners when a PR
# modifies matching files.
#
# Format:  <path-pattern>  <owner> [<owner> ...]
# Docs:    https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Global default — every PR requires review from the platform team.
# This acts as a safety net for agent-authored PRs: even if an agent
# opens a PR, a human from @EdwardRosenberg/platform-team must approve it.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*  @EdwardRosenberg/platform-team

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CI/CD and governance files — require an additional explicit review.
# These are high-impact files; accidental or agent-driven changes here
# could affect every downstream repository.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
